style="height:42.75pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><span><br/></span></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"/><div style="min-height:42.75pt;width:100%"><div><span><br/></span></div></div><div><span><br/></span></div><div><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Item&#160;2.02 Results of Operations and Financial Condition.</span></div><div style="margin-top:5pt;text-indent:24.75pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">On January 23, 2024, Baker Hughes Company (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) issued a news release announcing its financial results for the quarter and year ended December 31, 2023, a copy of which is furnished with this Form 8-K as Exhibit&#160;99.1 and incorporated herein by reference. In accordance with General Instructions B.2. of Form 8-K, the information shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for purposes of Section&#160;18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, nor shall it be deemed incorporated by reference in any filing under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, except as shall be expressly set forth by specific reference in such a filing.</span></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;text-indent:24.75pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Following the issuance of the news release and the filing of this current report on Form 8-K, the Company will hold a conference call on Wednesday, January 24, 2024 at 9:30 a.m. Eastern Time, 8:30 a.m. Central Time, to discuss the earnings announcement. This scheduled conference call was previously announced on December 12, 2023. The conference call will broadcast live via a webcast that can be accessed by visiting the Baker Hughes Company website at: </span><span style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">www.investors.bakerhughes.com</span><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">. An archived version of the webcast will be available on the Baker Hughes Company website for one month following the webcast.</span></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;text-indent:24.75pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">In addition to financial results determined in accordance with GAAP that were included in the news release, certain information discussed in the news release and to be discussed on the conference call could be considered non-GAAP financial measures (as defined under the Securities and Exchange Commission's ("SEC") Regulation&#160;G). Any non-GAAP financial measures should be considered in addition to, and not as an alternative for, or superior to, net income (loss), operating income (loss), cash flows or other measures of financial performance prepared in accordance with GAAP as more fully discussed in the Company&#8217;s financial statements and filings with the SEC. Reconciliations of such non-GAAP information to the closest GAAP measures are included in the news release.</span></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Item&#160;7.01 Regulation&#160;FD Disclosure.</span></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;text-indent:24.75pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">On January 23, 2024, the Company issued a news release, a copy of which is furnished with this Form 8-K as Exhibit&#160;99.1 and incorporated into this Item&#160;7.01 by reference. In accordance with General Instructions B.2. of Form 8-K, the information shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for purposes of Section&#160;18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended, nor shall it be deemed incorporated by reference in any filing under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, except as shall be expressly set forth by specific reference in such a filing.</span></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;text-indent:24.75pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New Roman',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">See Item&#160;2.02, &#8220;Results of Operations and Financial Condition.&#8221;</span></div><div style="margin-top:14pt"><span style="color:#000000;font-family:'Times New $2,544 million year-over-year.</font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;padding-left:18pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font year-over-year.</font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;padding-left:18pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:14.5pt">GAAP diluted EPS of $1.91 and adjusted diluted EPS* of $1.60, a 76% increase over 2022.</font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;padding-left:18pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:14.5pt">Cash flows from operating activities were $3.06 billion and free cash flow* of $2.05 billion, a 54% conversion rate from adjusted EBITDA*.</font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;padding-left:18pt;text-indent:-18pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8226;</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;padding-left:14.5pt">Shareholder distributions of $1.32 billion, including $538 million of share repurchases.</font></div><div style="margin-top:6pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">HOUSTON &#38; LONDON (January&#160;23, 2024) </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#8211; Baker Hughes Company (Nasdaq&#58; BKR) (Baker Hughes or the Company) announced results today for the fourth-quarter and full-year 2023.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#34;As we continue our journey, 2023 proved to be a pivotal year for Baker Hughes. We successfully removed $150 million of costs, realigned our Industrial &#38; Energy Technology (IET) segment, and recently launched actions to further streamline our Oilfield Services &#38; Equipment segment (OFSE). Our strategy to transform the way we operate is working. In 2023, our adjusted EBITDA* was up double digits for the third consecutive year and exceeded prior cycle's peak levels by 25%. I would like to thank our employees for their hard work and commitment to achieve our goals, delivering for our customers, and pushing the Company forward,&#34; said Lorenzo Simonelli, Baker Hughes chairman and chief executive officer.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#34;During the fourth quarter, adjusted EBITDA* came in above the mid-point of our guidance range due to continued operational improvement and full realization of the $150 million of cost-out. IET orders remained strong, exceeding $3 billion for the fifth consecutive quarter. Additionally, we were awarded more than $1 billion of contractual service agreements (CSA), while we booked the previously announced 9.6 MTPA Ruwais Liquefied Natural Gas (LNG) project in the United Arab Emirates.&#34;</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#34;In OFSE, we continue to demonstrate solid margin improvement, with segment EBITDA margin* increasing to 17.9% and Oilfield Services EBITDA margins* now exceeding 20% &#8211; both record margins. In new energy, orders of $169 million in the fourth quarter brought the full-year total to $750 million.&#34;</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#34;As you can see from our strong 2023 results, Baker Hughes is on its way to becoming a leaner and more efficient energy technology company. We continue to carefully execute our plan to drive margins meaningfully higher,&#34; concluded Simonelli.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">* Non-GAAP measure. See reconciliations in the section titled &#34;Reconciliation of GAAP to non-GAAP Financial Measures.&#34; </font></div><div style="height:45pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">1</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">(4)%</font></td></tr></table></div><div style="margin-top:12pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#34;F&#34; is used in when variance is above 100%. Additionally, &#34;U&#34; is used when variance is below (100)%.</font></div><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">* Non-GAAP measure. See reconciliations in the section titled &#34;Reconciliation of GAAP to non-GAAP Financial Measures.&#34; EBITDA margin is defined as EBITDA divided by revenue. Free cash flow conversion rate is defined as free cash flow divided by EBITDA.  </font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt;text-align:justify"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Certain columns and rows in our tables and financial statements may not sum up due to the use of rounded numbers. </font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Quarter Highlights</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The OFSE business segment secured two significant, multi-year integrated solutions contracts in Latin America for drilling, completions, and plug and abandonment services. One contract comprises offshore exploration, while the other is for land development. The awards reflect confidence in Baker Hughes' solutions, contributing to our strategy of strengthening the core by increasing market penetration.</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Strong orders performance continued across IET in the fourth quarter. In Gas Technology Equipment, momentum continues in the offshore market. Baker Hughes was awarded an important contract by SBM Offshore to provide turbogenerators, turbocompressors, electric motor-driven compressors, as well as commissioning spare parts, for a Floating Production, Storage and Offloading vessel (FPSO).</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Gas Technology Equipment also secured an important contract from a consortium for one electric motor driven sour gas booster compression package, to support the development of offshore natural gas fields in the Middle East. During the fourth quarter Baker Hughes also confirmed the previously announced award to supply two electric liquefaction systems for the 9.6 MTPA Ruwais LNG project in the United Arab Emirates, one of the first all-electric LNG projects in the Middle East.</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Gas Technology Services secured several orders across multiple geographies and applications, as well CSA commitments worth more than $1 billion primarily driven by LNG and offshore projects in North America and the Middle East. Also in the quarter, Gas Technology Services secured several important upgrade orders, particularly in Europe for both refinery and gas network applications to provide operators with solutions that can enable efficiency gains and emissions reduction.</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">IET's Industrial Solutions product line expanded the reach of its Cordant&#8482; digital solutions and reached a multi-year contract deal with Shell to centralize asset condition and performance monitoring (System 1</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:6.5pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;position:relative;top:-3.5pt;vertical-align:baseline">TM</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">) across 33 sites. India's Oil and Natural Gas Corporation Limited (ONGC) awarded IET a multi-year contract for asset health software </font></div><div style="height:45pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font Additionally, &#34;U&#34; is used when variance is below (100)%.</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Revenue for the quarter was $6,835 million, an increase of 3% sequentially and an increase of 16% year-over-year. The increase in revenue was driven by higher volume in both IET and OFSE.</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The Company's total book-to-bill ratio in the quarter was 1.0&#59; the IET book-to-bill ratio in the quarter was 1.1.</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Operating income on a GAAP basis for the fourth quarter of 2023 was $651 million. Operating income decreased $62 million sequentially and decreased $12 million year-over-year. Total segment operating income was $904 million for the fourth quarter of 2023, up 12% sequentially and up 14% year-over-year.</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Adjusted operating income (a non-GAAP measure) for the fourth quarter of 2023 was $816 million, which excludes adjustments totaling $165 million before tax. A complete list of the adjusting items and associated reconciliation from GAAP has been provided in Table 1a in the section titled &#34;Reconciliation of GAAP to non-GAAP Financial Measures.&#34; Adjusted operating income for the fourth quarter of 2023 was up 14% sequentially and up 18% year-over-year.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Depreciation and amortization for the fourth quarter of 2023 was $274 million.</font></div><div style="height:45pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font Results</font></div></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td></tr></table></div></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Adjusted EBITDA (a non-GAAP measure) for the fourth quarter of 2023 was $1,091 million, which excludes adjustments totaling $165 million before tax. See Table 1b in the section titled &#34;Reconciliation of GAAP to non-GAAP Financial Measures.&#34; Adjusted EBITDA for the fourth quarter was up 11% sequentially and up 15% year-over-year.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The sequential increase in adjusted operating income and adjusted EBITDA was driven by higher volume in IET and price in OFSE, partially offset by higher research and development (R&#38;D) spend in IET. The year-over-year increase in adjusted operating income and adjusted EBITDA was driven by volume and pricing in both segments and structural cost-out initiatives, partially offset by cost inflation in both segments, and higher equipment mix and higher R&#38;D spend in IET.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Corporate costs were $88 million in the fourth quarter of 2023, down 7% sequentially and down 12% year-over-year.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Other Financial Items</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Remaining Performance Obligations (RPO) in the fourth quarter ended at $33.5&#160;billion, an increase of $1.0&#160;billion from the third quarter of 2023. OFSE RPO was $3.5&#160;billion, down 2% sequentially, while IET RPO was $29.9&#160;billion, up 4% sequentially. Within IET RPO, Gas Technology Equipment RPO was $12.1&#160;billion and Gas Technology Services RPO was $14.8&#160;billion.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Income tax expense in the fourth quarter of 2023 was $72 million.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Other non-operating loss in the fourth quarter of 2023 was $84 million. Included in other non-operating loss were net mark-to-market loss in fair value for certain equity investments of $84 million.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">GAAP diluted earnings per share was $0.43. Adjusted diluted earnings per share was $0.51. Excluded from adjusted diluted earnings per share were all items listed in Table 1a as well as the &#34;other adjustments (non-operating)&#34; found in Table 1c in the section entitled &#34;Reconciliation of GAAP to non-GAAP Financial Measures.&#34;</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Cash flow from operating activities was $932 million for the fourth quarter of 2023. Free cash flow (a non-GAAP measure) for the quarter was $633 million. A reconciliation from GAAP has been provided in Table 1d in the section entitled &#34;Reconciliation of GAAP to non-GAAP Financial Measures.&#34;</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Capital expenditures, net of proceeds from disposal of assets, were $298 million for the fourth quarter of 2023. Capital expenditures, net of proceeds from disposal of assets, were $221 million for OFSE, and $71 million for IET.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">During the fourth quarter, we extended our $3 billion revolving credit facility by four years, which now has a maturity in November 2028, and used available cash to pay down the $650 million of senior notes that matured in December 2023.</font></div><div 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:bottom"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Baker Hughes Company News Release</font></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:bottom"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Baker Hughes Company Announces Fourth-Quarter and Full-Year 2023 Results</font></div></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td></tr></table></div></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">IET orders of $3,030 million for the fourth quarter decreased by $1,259 million, or 29% year-over-year. The decrease was driven primarily by the timing of Gas Technology Equipment orders which were down $1,157 million, or 47% year-over-year.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">IET revenue of $2,879 million for the quarter increased $554 million, or 24% year-over-year. The increase was driven primarily by Gas Technology Equipment, up $350 million or 41% year-over-year, and Climate Technology Solutions, up $140 million year-over-year.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Segment operating income before tax for the quarter was $412 million, up 9% year-over-year. Segment EBITDA for the quarter was $463 million, up $34 million, or 8% year-over-year. The year-over-year increase in segment operating income and EBITDA was primarily driven by higher volume and pricing partially offset by unfavorable mix as a result of higher Gas Technology Equipment growth, cost inflation and higher R&#38;D spend.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt;margin-top:12pt;text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">2023 Total Year Results</font></div><div style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Reconciliation of GAAP to non-GAAP Financial Measures</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Management provides non-GAAP financial measures because it believes such measures are widely accepted financial indicators used by investors and analysts to analyze and compare companies on the basis of operating performance (including adjusted operating income&#59; EBITDA&#59; EBITDA margin&#59; adjusted EBITDA&#59; adjusted net income attributable to Baker Hughes&#59; and adjusted diluted earnings per share) and liquidity (free cash flow) and that these measures may be used by investors to make informed investment decisions. Management believes that the exclusion of certain identified items from several key operating performance measures enables us to evaluate our operations more effectively, to identify underlying trends in the business, and to establish operational goals for certain management compensation purposes. Management also believes that free cash flow is an important supplemental measure of our cash performance but should not be considered as a measure of residual cash flow available for discretionary purposes, or as an alternative to cash flow from operating activities presented in accordance with GAAP.</font></div><div style="margin-top:9pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Table 1a. // Edgar(tm) Renderer was created by staff of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  Data and content created by government employees within the scope of their employment are not subject to domestic copyright protection. 17 U.S.C. 105.
var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}

/* Updated 2009-11-04 */

}

}
